A Nairobi court yesterday issued a warrant of arrest against a city lawyer for failing to appear in court to answer to charges of stealing Sh19 million belonging to her client in conveyancing involving a parcel of land. Chief magistrate Francis Andayi issued the arrest order against lawyer Caroline Wairimu Kimemia alias Caroline Wairimu Wanjithia. She was to take a plea on theft by agent charges against her. Kimemia is accused of stealing from her clients in a land transfer on January 14, 2014. She is also accused of making a sale agreement for the purchase of the land on August 14, 2013, and inserting a wrong purchase price. The case will be mentioned on February 7.